from typing import *   # --- py stmt 1
def f_gold(s: str) -> int:   # --- py stmt 2
    i = 0   # --- py stmt 3
    ans = 0   # --- py stmt 4
    chars = set()   # --- py stmt 5
    for j, c in enumerate(s):   # --- py stmt 6
        if c == ' ':   # --- py stmt 7
            continue   # --- py stmt 8
        elif c == '*':   # --- py stmt 9
            break   # --- py stmt 10
        while c in chars:   # --- py stmt 11
            chars.remove(s[i])   # --- py stmt 12
            i += 1   # --- py stmt 13
        chars.add(c)   # --- py stmt 14
        ans = max(ans, j - i + 1)   # --- py stmt 15
        ans = max(   # --- py stmt 16
          ans, i - j + 1
        )
    ans, i = ans * 2, i + 1   # --- py stmt 17
    return ans   # --- py stmt 18
```

from typing import *   # --- py stmt 1
def f_gold(s: str) -> int:   # --- py stmt 2
    n = len(s)   # --- py stmt 3
    dp1 = [[False] * n for _ in range(n)]   # --- py stmt 4
    for i in range(n - 1, -1, -1):   # --- py stmt 5
        for j in range(i, n):   # --- py stmt 6
            dp1[i][j] = s[i] == s[j] and (j - 1 < 3 or dp1[i + 1][j - 1])   # --- py stmt 7
    dp2 = [0] * n   # --- py stmt 8
    for i in range(n):   # --- py stmt 9
        if not dp1[0][i]:   # --- py stmt 10
            dp2[i] = i   # --- py stmt 11
            for j in range(1, i + 1):   # --- py stmt 12
                if dp1[j][i]:   # --- py stmt 13
                    dp2[i] = min(dp2[i], dp2[j - 1] + 1)   # --- py stmt 14
    return dp2[-1]   # --- py stmt 15
```

function find_min_insertions_to_form_palindrome(str) {   // --- py stmt 2
    let str_length = str.length;   // --- py stmt 3
    let is_palindrome = new Array(str_length);   // --- py stmt 4
    for (let i = 0; i < str_length; i++) {
        is_palindrome[i] = new Array(str_length).fill(false);   // --- py stmt 4
    }
    for (let i = str_length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {   // --- py stmt 5
        for (let j = i; j < str_length; j++) {   // --- py stmt 6
            is_palindrome[i][j] = str[i] == str[j] && (j - 1 < 3 || is_palindrome[i + 1][j - 1]);   // --- py stmt 7
        }
    }
    let min_insertions = new Array(str_length).fill(0);   // --- py stmt 8
    for (let i = 0; i < str_length; i++) {   // --- py stmt 9
        if (!is_palindrome[0][i]) {   // --- py stmt 10
            min_insertions[i] = i;   // --- py stmt 11
            for (let j = 1; j <= i; j++) {   // --- py stmt 12
                if (is_palindrome[j][i]) {   // --- py stmt 13
                    min_insertions[i] = Math.min(min_insertions[i], min_insertions[j - 1] + 1);   // --- py stmt 14
                }
            }
        }
    }
    return min_insertions[str_length - 1];   // --- py stmt 15
}
